name: "Nazar #3" by Cinthia Ponce
description:
A Turkish eye, also known as a nazar, is a bead in the shape of a flat drop containing the figure of an eye to which protective powers are attributed, and which is widely used as a talisman or amulet against the evil eye and bad energies.

Its original name, coming from the Turkish language, is nazar boncuğu, which means 'bead of the evil eye'.
